President Donald J. Trump spoke with President Emmanuel Macron of France about the decision to impose tariffs on steel and aluminum imports. Trump emphasized that the decision is necessary for national security. They also discussed alternative ways to address US concerns. The leaders also discussed Trump's intention to meet with North Korean leader Kim Jong Un for the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula. They condemned the Assad regime, as well as its Russian and Iranian sponsors, for the atrocities committed, including the bombing in East Ghouta.